    thinking: "**Designing Server Implementation**\n\nI\'m now focusing on `server.ts`. My initial approach involves prioritizing API route design. Specifically, I\'m thinking through endpoints like `/api/nexus`, `/api/generate-report`, and `/api/generate-workflow`. Next up, I want to consider incorporating Vite development integration if `process.env.NODE_ENV` isn\'t production.\n\n\n**Implementing Production-Ready Server**\n\nI\'ve made progress ensuring production static file serving from the `dist/` directory, along with a catch-all route to `dist/index.html`. Port 3000 and host `0.0.0.0` are set, and JSON request bodies are being parsed. I am now working on structuring the system instructions for Gemini, which includes injecting `erpData` to give it real-time access to the company\'s ERP database and state. The next step is working out the logic for the `/api/nexus` endpoint.\n\n\n**Addressing API Key Availability**\n\nI\'m now implementing lazy initialization of the GoogleGenAI client, only when needed within the API route handlers. This addresses the critical constraint of a potentially missing `process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY`. I\'ll incorporate error handling to throw a clear message if the key isn\'t present, preventing the application from crashing at startup.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `server.ts` file. It will handle the Express server setup, lazy initialization of the Gemini SDK to prevent startup crashes when keys are missing, implement `/api/nexus` for the chatbot, `/api/generate-report` for report generation, and `/api/generate-workflow` for automated workflow planning. It will also manage the Vite middleware for development and static assets serving for production."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 537560328
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
