  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Dashboard**\n\nI\'m currently focused on designing the dashboard within `App.tsx`. My focus has shifted towards the specific visual and functional components needed, starting with the sidebar layout. This includes the Cloud ERP logo, along with a \"hub\" or \"hive\" icon and a \"Dashboard\" entry, all utilizing the `lucide-react` library.\n\n\n**Refining Navigation Elements**\n\nI\'m now integrating \"Analytics\", \"Inventory\", \"Production\", \"Supply Chain\", and \"Settings\" links. I\'m prioritizing an appealing visual state for the active tab, including a soft grey background and a left blue border. Also adding a \"New Workflow\" blue button to trigger a workflow creator modal. Bottom links for support and documentation are also added, with custom popups.\n\n\n\n**Implementing Interactive Components**\n\nI\'ve been working on dynamic, interactive elements for the dashboard now. I\'m focusing on a KPI metrics row with hover states and trend badges, and interactive charts displaying projected vs. actual growth. A donut chart will visualize inventory status, with hover/click highlights. Finally, I\'m integrating a recent activities feed with actionable items.\n\n\n**Adding Quick Actions**\n\nI\'ve just added several quick action buttons to the dashboard, including \"Hire Employee,\" \"Create Invoice,\" and \"Generate Report,\" each triggering a specific form or modal. I\'ve also incorporated the \"Nexus AI\" widget, complete with a chatbot that interacts with the ERP\'s current state. This widget handles empty states and errors gracefully, guiding users through API key setup if needed. I\'ve configured the chat input to send requests to `/api/nexus` and stream Gemini\'s response.\n\nI\'m starting on the new views now!\n\n\n**Developing New Views**\n\nI\'m now integrating an interactive inventory view featuring robust search and filtering options, a high-density table with interactive \"Adjust Stock\" buttons, and a dynamic utilization percentage. There will be a low stock alert panel triggering AI-driven reorders. I\'m also developing a production view with a Kanban board layout for batch management, and drag-and-drop interactivity.\n\n\n**Expanding ERP Scope**\n\nI\'m presently integrating core functionality within the new Supply Chain View: shipment cards displaying vendor, route, estimated delivery, and status, coupled with a visual progress timeline. I\'ve also incorporated a \"Add Shipment\" form. Now, the settings view is under construction, including an AI model temperature control, system prompt adjustments, and a secret status indicator that checks the GEMINI_API_KEY. I\'ve also added the dark mode/light mode toggle.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will view the global `/src/index.css` file before editing to see how tailwind is imported and customize it."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 9
      nanos: 52859356
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
