  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Planning React Structure**\n\nI\'m now focusing on structuring the React application within `/src/App.tsx`. I\'m thinking about component breakdown to avoid exceeding token limits and keeping `/src/App.tsx` concise. Building beautiful sub-components seems like a solid approach to maintain readability. I also need to be thoughtful about how many lines I am creating.\n\n\n**Implementing Modular Components**\n\nI\'ve decided to move forward with creating modular component files. The framework\'s encouragement to separate logic and components into distinct files like `/src/components/Sidebar.tsx`, `/src/components/Header.tsx`, and `/src/components/DashboardView.tsx` (and others) is ideal. My goal is to maintain a manageable token count and enhance readability.\n\n\n**Defining View Components**\n\nI\'m now outlining key view components. I\'ll need an \"Executive Overview\" view with all the essential elements. \"AnalyticsView\" will contain detailed charts, while \"InventoryView\" focuses on inventory management. Production and Supply Chain views are also planned, with a Settings component to follow.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/DashboardView.tsx` file. It will render the \"Executive Overview\" dashboard exactly as shown in the screenshot, featuring:\n- Four interactive KPI Cards (clicking on them shows historical breakdowns).\n- A high-fidelity, fully interactive SVG Line and Area Chart for \"Revenue vs Expenses\" featuring rich linear gradients, custom dashed outlines, and a dynamic mouse-hover tooltip displaying precise financial stats for each month.\n- An interactive SVG Donut Chart representing \"Inventory Status\" (utilization, in-production, low-stock, and outbound counts).\n- A custom, scrollable Recent Activities feed with action icons and real-time alerts.\n- A Quick Actions Widget supporting live operations like launching a workflow, adding simulated staff, or creating billing invoices.\n- The **Nexus AI Interactive Chatbot** allowing the user to type questions about their actual ERP dataset and receive intelligent answers from the server-side Gemini API."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 668011695
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
